We spent 5 days in Hainan, visited some small islands. Although the national day holiday was already over, there were still lots of tourists. 

According to statistics, nearly 1 million tourists flocked into the island during the holiday, even 39% higher than that of 2019.

The tourism industry is recovering, and Hainan is so popular in China, especially among people from Dongbei (Northeast China). 

We heard Dongbei accent everywhere, tourists, Didi drivers, restaurant owners, and even guides. 😂😂😂
